  "description": "A safety tool is a method for signaling boundaries or discomfort during play in a [role-playing game](../index.md). Because role-playing games can engage intense or sensitive themes — violence, loss, betrayal, trauma — participants need ways to pause or redirect the fiction when it crosses personal limits.",
